article.description: — Tristen Newton scored a career-high 30 points as East Carolina beat Western Carolina 95-79 on Sunday.
article.headline: Newton lifts East Carolina over W. Carolina 95-79
article.linkText: Newton lifts East Carolina over W. Carolina 95-79
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- — Tristen Newton scored a career-high 30 points as East Carolina beat Western Carolina 95-79 on Sunday. Newton made 5 of 7 3-pointers while hitting 10 of 16 overall from the field. He also dished six assists and had six rebounds. Brandon Suggs added 15 points for East Carolina (3-0). Tremont Robinson-White added 14 points. Nick Robinson scored a career-high 28 points for the Catamounts (1-2). Marcus Banks added 13 points. Travion McCray had 11 points and Joe Petrakis 10. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25------ Information from: Automated Insights, http://automatedinsights.com/ ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
